iii. In the RLS district, a duplex dwelling shall not be located within 400
feet of another duplex dwelling, measured in a straight line from
the nearest lot lines of the two duplex dwellings.
llm_output.rationale: The section provides specific spacing requirements for duplex dwellings in the RLS district, but it does not provide a min_unit_size for single-family homes or a general min_unit_size for the RLS district.
